# Backlog implementation (6-code)

When asked to implement the **next backlog item**, follow this workflow.

## 1. Pick the item

1. Read [5-dev/backlog.md](../5-dev/backlog.md) — use **Suggested implementation order**; skip rows whose **Status** is not `Todo`.
2. Take the first eligible `BL-##`. Note its **Dependencies**, **Traces to**, mockups, and acceptance criteria.

## 2. Implement

1. Read cited parents: feature file, [building-blocks](../3-arch/building-blocks.md), [runtime-views](../3-arch/runtime-views.md), linked mockups/journeys, [testing-plan](../5-dev/testing-plan.md) `TC-##` rows.
2. Code under `6-code/` only — match ADRs.
3. Satisfy every acceptance criterion checkbox; add tests mapped to linked `TC-##`.
4. Run build/tests relevant to the item.

## 3. Close out

1. Mark acceptance criteria done and set **Status** → `Done` in [backlog.md](../5-dev/backlog.md).
2. On commit (if requested): message cites `BL-##` and `FR-…` IDs.

